Executive Summary



Safety and Environmental Policy:



At SSI Technologies, Inc., quality and environmental management means surpassing our customer's expectations for high quality performance, on-time delivery and value while maintaining a safe and healthy environment for our employees as well as our community by diligent prevention of pollution and waste. Our commitment to customer satisfaction is driven by accomplishing our objectives which include regulatory and customer requirements, continuously improving and the ongoing development of all team members including suppliers and contractors.



Facility Description and Regulated Substances Handled:



SSI's Sintered Specialties Division is the world's largest stainless steel powder metal components manufacturing facility. We specialize in high-temperature sintering of stainless steel, soft magnetic alloy, tool steel, sinter-hardening alloy, and custom powder metal parts. We are unique in the Powder Metal industry with our ability to offer four metal process technologies. We serve a diverse range of applications in diverse industries - Automotive, Industrial, Medical, and Ordnance.

The facility is located on a nominal five acre site, with paved shipping and receiving areas. The major structures and their designated functions are:

Receiving Area with docks;

Furnace Room;

Warehouse;

Shipping Area with docks;

Maintenance Room;

Office areas;



Bulk liquid hydrogen storage tanks (2) and liquid nitrogen storage tank (1) located outdoors.

The regulated process consists of two bulk liquid hydrogen storage tanks (with a total maximum capacity of 13,000 pounds of hydrogen), two hydrogen vaporizers, and the piping and control system for distributing gaseous hydrogen to the various furnaces used to manufacture sintered powder metal parts. The hydrogen is used to maintain the proper atmosphere within the furnaces for manufacture of quality metal parts. Integral to the regulated hydrogen process is the liquid nitroge

n process that provides instrument air for the pneumatically controlled hydrogen shutoff and control valves and nitrogen purge gas for the furnaces to prevent explosive gas mixtures within the furnaces. Safety features include redundant safety relief valves and rupture disks on the hydrogen storage tanks, a pressure control system on the tanks, multiple line pressure relieve valves, a line pressure regulating system, temperature controls, an excess flow valve, and an emergency stop button to rapidly close all pneumatic hydrogen valves. The liquid hydrogen storage system is continuously monitored by the supplier, Linde LLC, via telemetry. The furnace control systems include automatic hydrogen shutoff valves and nitrogen purge interlocks. The furnace building has an extensive ventilation system and a fire suppression system.



General Accident Release Prevention Program:



The facility has implemented a Process Safety Management / Risk Management Program (PSM/RMP Program) for its Hydrogen Process operation and maintenance. The PSM/RMP Program has been incorporated as both policy, and most importantly, procedure in everyday operations and maintenance. The bulk storage system is leased from Linde, LLC, who provides continuous monitoring of the system as well as periodic inspection and maintenance.

Among the many safety features present at the facility are:

EPA Risk Management Program and OSHA Process Safety Management Program;

Continuous monitoring of the hydrogen storage tank systems via telemetry by Linde, LLC;

Redundant safety relieve valves and rupture disks;

Hydrogen tank pressure control system;

Piping system pressure relief and temperature control;

Excess flow valve;

Emergency stop;

Automatic hydrogen shutoff valves and nitrogen purge systems at the furnaces;

Building ventilation and fire suppression system;

Emergency communication systems;

Training Programs, such as Chemical Safety, Safe-Work Practices, and others;

